    "biography": "<p>The Nightshade, Nightwing glides as a vast, jet-black bat with a 50-foot wingspread, its eyeless form unveiling all with magical perception. Crafted by greater evils, it stalks any terrain, its unmarred black expanse a portent of doom.</p><p>Daylight dims it with a -4 attack penalty, its aura spoiling consumables within 120', chilling the air for the wary. Immune to illusions, wands, poison, charm, hold, cold, spells below 6th level, and weapons below +3, it halves dragon breath damage (quarter with a save), regenerating [[/r 3 #Hit points per round]]. It silently casts charm person, invisibility, haste, confusion, cloudkill (21st-level magic-user), darkness, hold person, cause disease, dispel magic, and finger of death (21st-level cleric) at will.</p><p>Its swoop, with 90% surprise, strikes for [[/r 1d6+6 #Swoop damage]] plus poison (-2 save penalty), polymorphing victims into giant bats (save vs. spells or charmed). It drains one 'plus' from items with a +4 bonus attack, summons undead every 4 hours (1d6: 1-3 shade, 4-5 haunt, 6 hand druj), resists turning with a save vs. spells, and carries swallowed treasures.<br><b>Terrain:</b> Any</p>",
